 1627:         """
 1628:         Probes WDL tables for win/draw/loss-information.
 1629: 
 1630:         Probing is thread-safe when done with different *board* objects and
 1631:         if *board* objects are not modified during probing.
 1632: 
 1633:         Returns ``2`` if the side to move is winning, ``0`` if the position is
 1634:         a draw and ``-2`` if the side to move is losing.
 1635: 
 1636:         Returns ``1`` in case of a cursed win and ``-1`` in case of a blessed
 1637:         loss. Mate can be forced but the position can be drawn due to the
 1638:         fifty-move rule.
 1639: 
 1640:         >>> import chess
 1641:         >>> import chess.syzygy
 1642:         >>>
 1643:         >>> with chess.syzygy.open_tablebase("data/syzygy/regular") as tablebase:
 1644:         ...     board = chess.Board("8/2K5/4B3/3N4/8/8/4k3/8 b - - 0 1")
 1645:         ...     print(tablebase.probe_wdl(board))
 1646:         ...
 1647:         -2
 1648: 
 1649:         :raises: :exc:`KeyError` (or specifically
 1650:             :exc:`chess.syzygy.MissingTableError`) if the position could not
 1651:             be found in the tablebase. Use
 1652:             :func:`~chess.syzygy.Tablebase.get_wdl()` if you prefer to get
 1653:             ``None`` instead of an exception.
 1654:         """
